    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - Description - Hood</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Hood</title>
        <para>The fiberglass hood is a sculptured, three-piece hood with bonded fenders, and removable valance sections.
            The hood is a tilting type. The narrowed, streamlined, tilting, fiberglass hoods provide aerodynamics (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0901003">Figure 3</hotlnk>) and functional design styling, while still enclosing the air
            cleaner.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0901003" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. 3300 Hood Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. GRILLE / SHROUD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. INTERNATIONAL TRUCK AND ENGINE LOGO PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. 3300 SERIES HOOD</callout1>
                <callout1>4. COWL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>5. ENGINE AIR INTAKE OPENING</callout1>
                <callout1>6. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>7. FENDER VALANCE (BOLTED TO FENDER)</callout1>
                <callout1>8. UPPER FENDER ASSEMBLY (BONDED TO HOOD)</callout1>
                <callout1>9. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>10. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
